text: Kronoby () is a municipality in Ostrobothnia, Finland. It had about 6,700 people living there in January 2014. The municipalities next to it are Evijärvi, Kaustinen, Kokkola, Luoto, Pedersöre and Veteli. The municipality was established in 1607. == References == == Other websites == *The official page * Category:Municipalities of Ostrobothnia
